<https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_I1_FS_DbSyntaxFormats.ttl> a ftr:Metric, dqv:Metric, dcat:Resource ;
    dcterms:identifier "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_I1_FS_DbSyntaxFormats.ttl"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:isDefinedBy "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_I1_FS_DbSyntaxFormats.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcat:landingPage "https://ostrails.github.io/assessment-component-metadata-records/metric/FM_I1_FS_DbSyntaxFormats.ttl"^^xsd:anyURI ;
    dcterms:title "FAIR Metric - I1 - Metadata - Database adopts syntactic knowledge representation languages (registry evaluation)"^^xsd:string ;
    rdfs:label "FM_I1_FS_DbSyntaxFormats"^^xsd:string ;
    vivo:abbreviation "FM_I1_FS_DbSyntaxFormats"^^xsd:string ;
    dcterms:description """**What is being measured?**

This metric evaluates whether the database adopts syntactic knowledge representation languages [as defined by FAIRsharing](https://fairsharing.gitbook.io/fairsharing/fair-assistance/fair-support-and-definitions/syntactic-vs-semantic-knowledge-representation-languages). In FAIRsharing, this corresponds to the FAIRsharing record being linked to at least one model/format record classified as a syntactic knowledge representation language. Expected input is the DOI or URL of the registry (e.g. FAIRsharing) record under evaluation.

**Why should we measure it?**

I1 requires that (meta)data use a formal, accessible, shared and broadly applicable language for knowledge representation. This metric uses the relationships provided within FAIRsharing records to determine whether the database adopts formats that provide structured syntactic representations of information [as defined by FAIRsharing](https://fairsharing.gitbook.io/fairsharing/fair-assistance/fair-support-and-definitions/syntactic-vs-semantic-knowledge-representation-languages). Syntactic knowledge representation languages are important FAIR-enabling characteristics because they support the consistent exchange, interpretation, validation and reuse of information across systems.

This metric has similarities with **FAIR Metric - I1 - Metadata - Database-level knowledge representation languages (syntactic)**, which also evaluates the adoption of syntactic knowledge representation languages. Whereas that metric begins with a research object identifier and uses FAIRsharing as a source of evidence about the hosting database, this metric begins with a registry record identifier as part of a registry evaluation of the database itself."""^^xsd:string ;
    dcat:keyword "FAIR"^^xsd:string ;
    schema:about "Not applicable"^^xsd:string ;
    ftr:applicationArea <http://www.fairsharing.org/ontology/subject/SRAO_0000401> ;
    ftr:inDimension <https://w3id.org/fair/principles/terms/I1> ;
    dcat:version "1.0.0"^^xsd:string ;
    
    
    ftr:status "Active"@en ;
     
    
    
    
    
